    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but how can you \"create\" something that lasts when the laws of physics literally dictate that everything decays? even if I build something or love someone, the entropy always wins. it feels like we're just pretending. like we're all just playing a game that we know is rigged and ultimately meaningless. it's exhausting to keep up the act when the end result is always nothingness.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
